1 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
2 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
3 CONCURRING THEREIN:
4 THAT the State of Oklahoma be exempt from the provisions of the
5 Stark Law, 42 U.S.C., Section 1395nn, which adversely impact the
6 delivery of essential medical care in rural areas of the state.
7 THAT the State of Oklahoma be exempt from any administrative
8 rule adopted pursuant to the authority of the Stark Law, 42 U.S.C.,
9 Section 1395nn, which adversely impacts the delivery of essential
10 medical care in rural areas of the state.
